import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Sample data (replace this with your actual data loading code)
data = {
'DistanceFromHome': [1, 2, 10, 20, 30],
'YearsAtCompany': [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],
'Attrition': ['Yes', 'No', 'Yes', 'No', 'Yes']
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Ensure 'Attrition' column is categorical
if 'Attrition' in df.columns:
df['Attrition'] = df['Attrition'].astype('category')
else:
print("The 'Attrition' column does not exist. Please check the column names.")

# Plotting the scatter plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(x='DistanceFromHome', y='YearsAtCompany', hue='Attrition', data=df, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Scatterplot of DistanceFromHome vs YearsAtCompany')
plt.xlabel('Distance From Home')
plt.ylabel('Years at Company')
plt.legend(title='Attrition')
plt.show()
[74]:
#Data Cleaning
#Data cleaning involves handling missing values, correcting data types, and removing or fixing erroneous data.
# Fill missing values for categorical and numeric columns separately
for column in df.columns:
if df[column].dtype == 'object' or df[column].dtype.name == 'category':
df[column] = df[column].fillna(df[column].mode()[0])
else:
df[column] = df[column].fillna(df[column].mean())
[75]:
# Convert object types to category
for column in df.select_dtypes(include='object').columns:
df[column] = df[column].astype('category')

# If 'Attrition' is not already in the dataset, we skip this step
if 'Attrition' in df.columns:
df['Attrition'] = df['Attrition'].astype('category')
else:
print("The 'Attrition' column does not exist. Please check the column names.")
[78]:
#Data Encoding
#Handle label encoding and one-hot encoding:

from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

# Encoding categorical columns
label_encoders = {}
categorical_columns = df.select_dtypes(include='category').columns

for col in categorical_columns:
le = LabelEncoder()
df[col] = le.fit_transform(df[col])
label_encoders[col] = le

# One-hot encoding
df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=categorical_columns, drop_first=True)
